<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L2' title='View on GitHub'>2</a>   module Backwards</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L3' title='View on GitHub'>3</a>     module CommonsOnlySittingDays</code></pre>


<p>The calculation counts a day whenever the House of Commons has an actual sitting day - and requires the start date and the number of days to count.</p>

<p>The calculation is set out in <a href="https://www.legislation.gov.uk/ukpga/2008/29/section/5#section-5-4A">section 5 (4A) of the Planning Act 2008</a>.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L9' title='View on GitHub'>9</a>       def commons_only_sitting_days_reverse( date, target_day_count )</code></pre>
<p>We set the scrutiny start date, being the start date of the calculation and the end date of the scrutiny period.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L12' title='View on GitHub'>12</a>         @scrutiny_start_date = nil</code></pre>
<p>We go forward one day.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L15' title='View on GitHub'>15</a>         date = date.next</code></pre>
<p>We set the day count to zero.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L18' title='View on GitHub'>18</a>         day_count = 0</code></pre>
<p>Whilst the number of days we’re counting is less than the target number of days to count ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L21' title='View on GitHub'>21</a>         while ( day_count &lt; target_day_count ) do</code></pre>
<p>... continue to the <strong>previous day</strong>.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L24' title='View on GitHub'>24</a>           date = date.prev_day</code></pre>
<p>If the date is actual sitting day in the House of Commons ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L27' title='View on GitHub'>27</a>           if date.is_commons_actual_sitting_day?</code></pre>
<p>... we set the scrutiny start date to this date if the scrutiny start date is nil ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L30' title='View on GitHub'>30</a>             @scrutiny_start_date = date if @scrutiny_start_date.nil?</code></pre>
<p>... and add 1 to the day count.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L33' title='View on GitHub'>33</a>             day_count +=1</code></pre>
<p>Otherwise, if the calendar has no record of what type of day this is, we can&#39;t calculate the end date, ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L36' title='View on GitHub'>36</a>           elsif date.is_calendar_not_populated?</code></pre>
<p>... this error message is displayed to users ...</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L39' title='View on GitHub'>39</a>             @error_message = &quot;It&#39;s not currently possible to calculate an anticipated start date, as that date occurs during a period for which no sitting day information is available.&quot;</code></pre>
<p>... and we stop looking through the calendar.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L42' title='View on GitHub'>42</a>             break</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L43' title='View on GitHub'>43</a>           end</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L44' title='View on GitHub'>44</a>         end</code></pre>
<p>We return the calculated date.</p>

<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L47' title='View on GitHub'>47</a>         date</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L48' title='View on GitHub'>48</a>       end</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L49' title='View on GitHub'>49</a>     end</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L50' title='View on GitHub'>50</a>   end</code></pre>
<pre><code><a href='https://github.com/ukparliament/egg-timer/blob/main/app/lib/calculations/backwards/commons_only_sitting_days.rb#L51' title='View on GitHub'>51</a> end</code></pre>

